EX 11

Question:
Check the validity of the following relationships:

a) det( [ [a + b,  b],
[c + d,  d] ] ) = det( [ [a, b],
[c, d] ] )

b) det( [ [a + b*x,  b],
[c + d*x,  d] ] ) = det( [ [a, b],
[c, d] ] )

Solution:

a)
Left side = (a + b)d - b(c + d)
= ad + bd - bc - bd
= ad - bc
Right side = ad - bc
So it is TRUE.

b)
Left side = (a + b*x)d - b(c + d*x)
= ad + bdx - bc - bdx
= ad - bc
Right side = ad - bc
So it is TRUE for all x.

